    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just so annoying because it was working fine yesterday. it feels like something just randomly died for no reason. is there anything else that could cause that weird humming if it's not the capacitor?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's frustrating when things just stop working, especially when they were fine yesterday! If the capacitor isn't the cause, the humming could be coming from a seized motor bearing, which is like a little mechanical blockage inside the motor itself. Another possibility is a problem with the fan motor windings, meaning the electricity isn't flowing correctly through the motor coils. Sometimes, even a loose connection somewhere in the wiring harness can cause the motor to try and start but just hum instead of spinning.",
      "source": "target",
